### 8.14 *Twinkle Twinkle*, Jazzed: The Chapter's Finale Artifact

We've played *Twinkle* on piano (Chapter 3), harmonized it (Chapter 6), and voiced it with section timbres (Chapter 7). Now we **jazz it**: a Rhodes-like melody with a warm, detuned organ bass and a lush pad harmony.

```scheme
;; *[needs: GAP-3]* — full envelope/detune/filter control

;; Rhodes melody voice
(define (rhodes pitch dur)
  (let ((detunes '(-2 2)))
    (for-each
      (lambda (dt)
        (note/strike pitch dur 0.65
          :attack 0.06 :decay 0.15 :sustain 0.5 :release 0.3
          :detune dt))
      detunes)))

;; Organ bass voice
(define (organ-bass pitch dur)
  (let ((detunes '(-3 0 3)))
    (for-each
      (lambda (dt)
        (note/strike pitch dur 0.5
          :attack 0.005 :sustain 1.0 :release 0.01
          :detune dt
          :filter 'lowpass :cutoff 2800))
      detunes)))

;; Pad harmony voice
(define (pad-chord pitches dur)
  (for-each
    (lambda (pitch)
      (let ((detunes '(-6 0 6)))
        (for-each
          (lambda (dt)
            (note/strike pitch dur 0.3
              :attack 0.8 :decay 0.4 :sustain 0.75 :release 1.5
              :detune dt
              :filter 'lowpass :cutoff 1600))
          detunes)))
    pitches))

;; Twinkle Twinkle, bar by bar
(define (twinkle-jazzed)
  ;; Bar 1: \"Twin-kle twin-kle\"
  (rhodes 'C4 'quarter) (rhodes 'C4 'quarter)
  (organ-bass 'C2 'half)
  (pad-chord '(E3 G3 C4) 'half)
  
  (rhodes 'G4 'quarter) (rhodes 'G4 'quarter)
  (organ-bass 'C2 'half)
  
  ;; Bar 2: \"lit-tle star\"
  (rhodes 'A4 'quarter) (rhodes 'A4 'quarter)
  (organ-bass 'F2 'half)
  (pad-chord '(F3 A3 C4) 'half)
  
  (rhodes 'G4 'half)
  (organ-bass 'C2 'half)
  (pad-chord '(E3 G3 C4) 'half)
  
  ;; Bar 3: \"How I won-der\"
  (rhodes 'F4 'quarter) (rhodes 'F4 'quarter)
  (organ-bass 'F2 'half)
  (pad-chord '(F3 A3 C4) 'half)
  
  (rhodes 'E4 'quarter) (rhodes 'E4 'quarter)
  (organ-bass 'C2 'half)
  (pad-chord '(E3 G3 C4) 'half)
  
  ;; Bar 4: \"what you are\"
  (rhodes 'D4 'quarter) (rhodes 'D4 'quarter)
  (organ-bass 'G2 'half)
  (pad-chord '(D3 G3 B3) 'half)
  
  (rhodes 'C4 'half)
  (organ-bass 'C2 'half)
  (pad-chord '(E3 G3 C4) 'whole))

(twinkle-jazzed)
```

`<!-- BUILD: once GAP-3 is closed, this example produces a three-voice (melody/bass/pad) jazzed arrangement of Twinkle with distinct timbres per voice -->`

[VISUAL: A jazz club stage at night. A Rhodes keyboard (center), a B3 organ (left), and a synthesizer (right, glowing pads). The runtime stands at the Rhodes, blossom sprites at the other instruments. Musical staff above showing the first two bars of Twinkle in three-part harmony (treble clef melody, bass clef bass line, middle harmony). Note-sprites bop on the staff in time with the sounding music.]

This is **the same melody** we learned in Chapter 3 — but now it *breathes, swells, and swings*. The timbre is the music.

