### 8.40 The Full Toolkit: A Multi-Timbral Ensemble Passage

Bring it all together: multiple voices, each with its own envelope, detune, filter, and modulation profile.

```scheme
;; *[needs: GAP-3]* — full parameter set

;; Voice 1: Rhodes melody
(define (rhodes pitch dur)
  (let ((detunes '(-2 2)))
    (for-each
      (lambda (dt)
        (note/strike pitch dur 0.6
          :attack 0.06 :decay 0.15 :sustain 0.5 :release 0.3
          :detune dt))
      detunes)))

;; Voice 2: Synth pad harmony
(define (pad-note pitch dur)
  (let ((detunes '(-8 0 8)))
    (for-each
      (lambda (dt)
        (note/strike pitch dur 0.35
          :attack 0.9 :decay 0.4 :sustain 0.75 :release 1.8
          :detune dt
          :filter 'lowpass :cutoff 1500
          :vibrato-rate 5.5 :vibrato-depth 6))
      detunes)))

;; Voice 3: Percussive bass
(define (bass-note pitch dur)
  (note/strike pitch dur 0.75
    :attack 0.01 :decay 0.2 :sustain 0.1 :release 0.05
    :filter 'lowpass :cutoff 900))

;; A four-bar passage
(define (ensemble-passage)
  ;; Bar 1
  (rhodes 'E4 'quarter) (bass-note 'E2 'quarter)
  (pad-note 'G3 'half) (pad-note 'B3 'half)
  (rhodes 'G4 'quarter) (bass-note 'E2 'quarter)
  (rhodes 'B4 'quarter) (bass-note 'B1 'quarter)
  (rhodes 'E5 'quarter)
  
  ;; Bar 2
  (bass-note 'A1 'half)
  (pad-note 'C3 'half) (pad-note 'E3 'half) (pad-note 'A3 'half)
  (rhodes 'C5 'quarter) (rhodes 'A4 'quarter)
  (rhodes 'E4 'half))

(ensemble-passage)
```

`<!-- BUILD: multi-voice ensemble with distinct timbral profiles -->`

[VISUAL: A small stage with three sections: a Rhodes keyboard (left), a synthesizer (center, glowing pads), and a bass amp (right). The runtime conducts from the center. Musical staff above showing the three-voice score. Note-sprites bop on their respective staves.]

Three voices, three timbres, one cohesive sound.

