### 8.19  A breathy flute melody — noise + tone layered

Let's combine several techniques: a flute-like tone (gentle harmonics), a shaped noise layer (breath transient), and a melody with varied articulation (some notes breathy, some pure).

```scheme
;; Flute tone (from 8.13).
(define flute-tone
  (let ((v (voice/create 'flute-tone)))
    (voice/waveform v (createPeriodicWave (list 1.0 0.2 0.05 0.02)))
    (voice/envelope v (adsr 0.05 0.1 0.7 0.2))
    (voice/filter v 'lowpass 3000 0.5)
    v))

;; Breath layer (noise with short envelope).
;; *[needs: GAP-3]* for shaped noise; we'll approximate with sfx for now.
(define (play-breathy-note pitch dur velocity)
  ;; Play the flute tone.
  (note/strike pitch dur velocity flute-tone)
  ;; Add a breath transient (sfx noise, but it's not envelope-shaped yet).
  (sfx 'noise))  ;; this is a placeholder; real version would layer shaped noise

;; A simple melody: D5 E5 F5 E5 D5 (quarter notes).
(play-breathy-note 'D5 'quarter 0.65)
(at-beat 1 (play-breathy-note 'E5 'quarter 0.65))
(at-beat 2 (play-breathy-note 'F5 'quarter 0.65))
(at-beat 3 (play-breathy-note 'E5 'quarter 0.65))
(at-beat 4 (play-breathy-note 'D5 'quarter 0.65))
```

